# README

## Overview

This capsule contains the code and data necessary to reproduce the core analytical workflow described in the manuscript. Specifically, it supports the reproduction of the following items:

Item 1, Figure 1: 
- Trend plots illustrating the frequency, duration, and intensity of atmospheric and riverine heatwaves
- Embedded maps showing the spatial distribution of these heatwave characteristics

### Important note on figure layout
The final multi-panel figures in the manuscript were assembled and refined manually using Adobe Illustrator, following the generation of individual panels by the code. As such, this capsule reproduces the individual panel plots, not the exact final layout or composite panels as they appear in the manuscript.

In addition, due to differences in package versions between the Code Ocean and local desktop environments, the figures generated here may exhibit minor aesthetic variations from those in the submitted manuscript. The underlying results and conclusions remain unchanged.

---

## Capsule structure

This capsule is organized into three main parts:

### 1) `code/`
Contains the R scripts for reproducing the core analyses.

Recommended execution order (scripts are numbered sequentially):
- `00.run_first.R` — entry script / initialization
- `01.detect_AHW.R` — detect atmospheric heatwaves (AHWs)
- `02.detect_RHW.R` — detect riverine heatwaves (RHWs)
- `03.detect_ARCH.R` — detect atmospheric–riverine compound heatwaves (ARCH)
- `04.analyze_RHW_AHW_trend.R` — trend analysis for AHW/RHW metrics (used for Figure 1-type outputs)
- `05.analyze_ARCH_trend.R` — ARCH trend analysis
- `06.plot_ARCH_example.R` — example plotting script (ARCH event visualization)

Additional files:
- `README` — this file
- `run` — Code Ocean runtime script (if applicable in this capsule)

---

### 2) `data/`
Contains input datasets and intermediate structured data used by the scripts.

Main data items include:
- `temp_WT.csv` — temperature / water temperature input data
- `tmax_US_LamaH.csv` — atmospheric temperature input (US + LamaH-related source)
- `AHW_attributes/` — processed attributes for atmospheric heatwave analyses
- `RHW_attributes/` — processed attributes for riverine heatwave analyses
- `ARCH_frequency_by_time_gap/` — ARCH frequency results under different time-gap settings

> Note: Some datasets are organized as folders because they contain multiple files/tables used at different analysis steps.

---

### 3) `results/`
Contains reproducible outputs generated by the scripts.

This folder should include the main plots for Figure 1 and 3, and subfolders for supporting materials (data/outputs/supplementary figures). Specifically:
- Figure 1, trend plots
- Figure 1, embeded maps
- Figure 3, xxx
- Subfolders, xxx

---


